    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "There is a strong relationship between cardiovascular system and SARS-CoV-2. The virus could affect cardiovascular system by several mechanisms: direct myocardial injury, systemic inflammation, altered myocardial demand-supply ratio, plaque rupture and coronary thrombosis, adverse effects of various therapies (i.e., prolonged QT interval) and electrolyte imbalances [19].",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 369,
                    "end": 371,
                    "mention": "19",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF10"
                }
            ],
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Patients with previous cardiovascular disease (CVD) appear to be more inclined to develop COVID-19 and have more severe clinical disease with worse outcome [19]. Previous cardiovascular disease, are associated with threefold greater risk of severe COVID 19 disease requiring in many cases intensive cares. Similarly, several cardiovascular risk factors (i.e., diabetes and hypertension) adversely affect prognosis of these patients.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 157,
                    "end": 159,
                    "mention": "19",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF10"
                }
            ],
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "We cannot exclude that quarantine stress could lead to Takotsubo Syndrome due to the sympathetic nervous system hyper-activation. A case of myocarditis, as a possible late phenomenon of the COVID 19 respiratory infection, has recently been reported from a group of Brescia hospital [20].",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 283,
                    "end": 285,
                    "mention": "20",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF12"
                }
            ],
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "And finally the quarantine for containing the Covid 19 outbreaks affect cardiovascular risk factors leading to an increase of cardiovascular risk burden.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "ref_spans": []
        }
    ],
